.TH CORTEX-AGENT 1 "2026-03-27" "cortex-agent 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cortex-agent \- Command-line tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cortex-agent
[
B-h
    R | 
        B--help
               R]
.br
.B cortex-agent

ICOMMAND
        R [
           ISUBCOMMAND
                      R] [
                          IARGS
                               R...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cortex-agent
.SH COMMANDS
Available commands:
.TP
.B list
List available agents
.TP
.B status
Show active agents
.TP
.B activate
Activate one or more agents
.TP
.B deactivate
Deactivate one or more agents
.TP
.B deps
Show dependency information for an agent
.TP
.B graph
Display dependency graph for agents
.TP
.B validate
Validate agent metadata against schema
.TP
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT
Override for context directory (set automatically by Claude Code when running plugin commands)
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.claude/
Default context directory containing agents, modes, rules, and other configuration
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cortex-agent-tui (1),
.BR cortex-agent-workflow (1)
